<b>Fire Bolt</b> is an <a href="/wiki/Evocation" title="Evocation" class="mw-redirect">evocation</a> <a href="/wiki/Cantrip" title="Cantrip" class="mw-redirect">cantrip</a> available to <a href="/wiki/Sorcerer" title="Sorcerer">sorcerers</a> and <a href="/wiki/Wizard" title="Wizard">wizards</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-spellLists_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-spellLists-1">[2]</a></sup>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Description"> Description </span></h2>
<p>You hurl a small flame at a <a href="/wiki/Creature" title="Creature">creature</a> or object, making a ranged spell attack. The target takes 1d10 <a href="/wiki/Fire" title="Fire" class="mw-redirect">fire</a> damage on hit. The fire ignites any flammable object hit by it that isn't being worn or carried.<sup id="cite_ref-spellDesc_0-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-spellDesc-0">[1]</a></sup>
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Leveling">Leveling</span></h3>
<p>The spell's number of damage dice increases by one at levels 5, 11, and 17.<sup id="cite_ref-spellDesc_0-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-spellDesc-0">[1]</a></sup>
</p>
